history.text: hello
Hey, that was an awesome movie!
It was fully deserving of it's pretty good reviews in my opinion.
i enjoyed the movie as well. Great show

Definitely, he carried the movie!
Yes he was amazing

I wonder where Jordan would've been if he never got that penny stocks job?
He was such an ambitious character that instead of stocks, it'd be a movie about selling boats or whatever lol.
Thats one of the things you always wonder. I like how the movie leaves that for you to wonder like that ebcause you can put your own spin on what you think would of happened
WIth him being ambitious like that, he could of done anything
Yeah, definitely. The character had such a drive though, that he would've succeeded in anything. yup
I especially liked how he recruited Donnie Azoff. Much different than most job interviews lol.

True but when you're dealing with that much $, the line between legal and illegal gets very blurry. Just depends on if you get caught.
Yeah, the tax man is the public enemy #1, these guys will anything to avoid taxes lol.
Thats true, they def brought attention on themselves with that one
Also to keep it out of the FBI's hands.
You eventually always get caught though
Yup, even if it's not for the charges that you were really guilty for.

I think Jordan 
got off really easy too. Only three years in minimum security.

especially after breaching his co operation deal
